Shanghailanders Exhibit Changing Consumer Psychology
SHANGHAI , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- " Need " and " brand " have replaced " price " as the most important factor influencing the shopping decisions of Shanghailanders , according to a survey by the Shanghai Statistics Bureau .
The survey revealed that 64 percent of 500 urban families questioned pay little attention to discounts , but instead equate price with quality .
Fourteen percent cited " need " as the reason for purchasing color television sets and air conditioners during 1997 , with less than eight percent citing low prices .
An increasing number of customers are paying more attention to brand name goods , according to the survey .
Experts attribute changing shopping habits to the maturation of the local consumer psychology .
